Package arduino_simulator.sensors

Class SensorEntry

java.lang.Object
arduino_simulator.sensors.SensorEntry
public class SensorEntry extends Object
class contains basic sensor's requirements for functioning, its limitations and similary, basically it is kind of metadata for sensor part of this data is shared on the initial handshake performed when we connect to the device driver

  • Constructor Details

    • SensorEntry

      public SensorEntry(SensorType sensorType, int sensorID, int dataSampleByteLength)
      As driver developer use this class
      Parameters:
      sensorType - specify type of the sensor, if your sensor type is not in the list of available sensor types, use CUSTOM_SENSOR type
      sensorID - specify id of each sensor you register
      dataSampleByteLength - specify length from your sensor's data sample in bytes
